                            <comment id="14580727" author="dholmes" created="Wed, 10 May 2023 21:02:49 -0700"  >Just to be clear this logic is all about performing cleanup aka &amp;quot;finalization&amp;quot; in two cases:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
1. When an object becomes unreachable&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;- This was true finalization that is now handled by Cleaners&lt;br/&gt;
2. At VM termination&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;- This was once implemented by runFinalizationAtExit() but that got removed and so the FinalizerThread was created which is installed as a shutdownHook (and so runs at VM exit) and which performs the cleanup for each registered Finalizable instance.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
I think the code could further be simplified by doing away with the Finalizable interface and only having the FinalizableObject class. Any class that can&amp;#39;t extend FinalizableObject would just have a FinalizableObject instance field that calls cleanup on its enclosing instance.&lt;br/&gt;
</comment>
